r.in.bin is similar to r.in.ascii.

It enables to import binary data from:

	ftp://edcftp.cr.usgs.gov/pub/data (gtopo30 or glcc).

in a region with (x, y) coordinates.

Example:

r.in.bin -s input=E020N90.DEM output=gtopo30 bytes=2 north=90 south=40 east=60 west=20 r=6000 c=4800 subst=-9999,0

Jacques Bouchard <bouchard@onera.fr> 
07.07.98
